    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1974-01-21T10:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1974-01-21T10:44:00-05:00" n="285"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                <head>285. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Saudi Arabia</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d285fn1">Source: Library of Congress,
                        Manuscript Division, <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>
                        Papers, Box CL 207, Geopolitical Files, Saudi Arabia, 4 Jan–6 Feb 74.
                        Secret; Flash; <gloss target="#t_Cherokee1">Cherokee</gloss>; <gloss
                            target="#t_Exdis1">Exdis</gloss>; Handle as <gloss target="#t_Nodis1"
                            >Nodis</gloss>. Drafted from a text by <persName corresp="#p_KHA1"
                            >Kissinger</persName> received from the White House. The White House
                        draft, January 21, is in the National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1"
                            >Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> Files, <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>
                        Office Files, Box 139, Country Files, Middle East, Saudi Arabia, Dec 73–Feb
                        74.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1974-01-21T15:44:00+00:00">January 21, 1974,
                        1544Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12869. Subject: Oil Boycott. <gloss target="#t_Ref1">Ref</gloss>: Jidda 329.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d285fn2">
                        <ref target="#d284">Document 284</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Approach taken in <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss> is absolutely
                        correct.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>In addition, you should tell <persName corresp="#p_SSO1">Saqqaf</persName>
                        and <persName corresp="#p_FIAAA1">Fahd</persName> that if the boycott is not
                        lifted by the time the Israelis are ready to withdraw, we may very well
                        recommend that Israel not commence its withdrawals. In addition, under these
                        circumstances we would be forced to stop all further efforts toward peace in
                        the Middle East. You should emphasize that we have fulfilled every promise
                        that we have made. It is now up to the Saudis and their Arab colleagues to
                        keep their own commitments. You cannot be too strong in your
                        representations.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>The above has been personally approved by the President.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>If it is not possible to deliver message in Saudi Arabia January 22, it
                        should be delivered as soon as possible January 23.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Kissinger</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
